no.motif.f

Interface Fn<I,O>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - the type of the function argument
    O - The type of object the function returns.
    All Superinterfaces:
    PartialApplicableTo<Fn0<O>>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Mapper<I,O>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FnChain, PartialApplication, PassThruIfNullOrElse

    public interface Fn<I,O>
extends PartialApplicableTo<Fn0<O>>
    Function taking a value of type I and returning a value of type O. 
     ƒ(I) ∈ O

    This function type is often referred to as a "mapper" or "transformer", as it takes one value and based on it, yields another value. The function defines the mapping between values.

    This function type is the most commonly used one, and is promoted to be named without an index, whereas the other function types are named as FnX, where X denotes how many arguments it takes. I.e. Fn0, Fn2, etc.
